word: the north york moors national park

body_content.explanation: a national park (= a large area of land protected by the government because of its natural beauty or because it has a special history) in the northern part of England:
examples: The North York Moors National Park was designated in 1952, through the National Parks and Access to the Countryside Act 1949.
Learn to canoe in the North York Moors National Park!
